# graphify-version.pin ‚Äî pinned upstream `graphifyy` CLI version (R4/S16)
#
# WHAT THIS PINS
#   The exact, verbatim stdout of `graphify --version` for the installed
#   upstream `graphifyy` pip package this repo's graph was last built or
#   verified against. D75: `graphifyy` is NEVER modified by specseyal ‚Äî
#   this file only RECORDS its version; it is a drift TRIPWIRE, not a
#   dependency lock/vendor file. `graphifyy` stays an ordinary versioned
#   pip dependency (D75, archivable per D29).
#
#   Currently pinned: graphifyy 0.8.44 (live-verified via `graphify
#   --version` -> "graphify 0.8.44").
#
# HOW THE VERSION IS OBTAINED AT CHECK TIME
#   Run `graphify --version` and capture its stdout VERBATIM (trim only
#   a trailing newline ‚Äî no other normalization, no token-extraction,
#   no regex pulling out just the semver). `importlib.metadata.version
#   ("graphifyy")` is NOT used as the check-time source ‚Äî it is not
#   reliably available on every host this pipeline runs on. The
#   installed CLI's own `--version` output is the sole source of truth,
#   both here and at check time.
#
# THE PREVENTIVE-CHECK CONTRACT (R4/S16 ‚Äî binding on T016's refresh.sh)
#   plan.md, Risks: "R4 ‚Äî Upstream graphifyy drift... upgraded to
#   preventive, not reactive". Before refresh.sh calls the upstream
#   `build_merge`/`detect_incremental` (Arm 2), it MUST, in this order:
#
#     1. Read this file's `pinned_graphify_version` value (extraction
#        one-liner below ‚Äî grepping/cutting is sufficient; sourcing the
#        file also works, since the payload line is valid POSIX sh).
#     2. Run `graphify --version` and capture its stdout verbatim.
#     3. Compare the two with PLAIN STRING EQUALITY. Do not parse a
#        version number out of either side first ‚Äî pin and compare the
#        full raw strings, so ANY drift in the CLI's version-string
#        output (not only a semver bump) trips the check. This is the
#        deliberately conservative, fail-closed reading of R4: a false
#        "mismatch" only costs a full regen; a false "match" risks a
#        silent wrong-contract `build_merge`/`detect_incremental` call.
#
#   - MATCH -> proceed to the normal S02 stale-branch table (cheap
#     `refresh.sh` incremental, or prune+targeted-re-extract, as
#     staleness dictates). This pin does not replace the freshness
#     check (`freshness.sh`) ‚Äî it gates entry to
#     `build_merge`/`detect_incremental` specifically, once staleness
#     has already routed there.
#   - MISMATCH ‚Äî including `graphify --version` failing, printing
#     nothing, or `graphify` being absent from PATH entirely ‚Äî refresh.sh
#     MUST take the FULL-REGEN branch of the S02 table. Never fall
#     through to `build_merge`/`detect_incremental` with an unverified
#     version: that silent wrong-contract call is exactly what this pin
#     exists to prevent (R4, upgraded preventive-not-reactive per S16).
#     Fail-closed: an unverifiable version (command missing/erroring)
#     is treated exactly like a confirmed mismatch, never like a match.
#
# HOW THIS FILE IS UPDATED
#   Only by a deliberate, reviewed edit when the upstream `graphifyy`
#   package is intentionally upgraded: re-run `graphify --version`,
#   paste its exact new stdout as the value below, commit. refresh.sh
#   (T016) only READS this file ‚Äî it must never auto-rewrite the pin
#   itself, or a genuine contract break would silently re-pin itself
#   away instead of routing to full-regen.
#
# EXTRACTION (POSIX sh, no sourcing required):
#   pinned=$(grep '^pinned_graphify_version=' graphify-version.pin | head -n1 | cut -d'"' -f2)
#
# (The payload line below is also valid POSIX sh variable-assignment
# syntax, so ". graphify-version.pin" works too and sets
# $pinned_graphify_version directly ‚Äî either form is an acceptable
# reading of this contract; pick whichever fits refresh.sh's own style
# and stay consistent within that script.)

pinned_graphify_version="graphify 0.8.44"
